div.div: 1b API calls opba-banking-protocol-facade, facade selects protocol and action to process the request
1c Protocol facade generates ServiceContext to call protocol. Protocol world view is limited to ServiceContext
1d Protocol Action (using bank-protocol-api) is called with ServiceContext (i.e. ListAccounts)
1e Protocol returns the result (i.e. List of accounts or Redirection if no consent is present)
1f Protocol result is handled and translated (i.e. for Redirection result authorization session is created
1i Banking API translates Facade result to 200 or 202 ResponseEntity with status code and returns to FinTech
1j Fintech asks user to enter consent authorization in OpenBanking
2a User calls Consent API to get consent status or to update it
2b API calls opba-banking-protocol-facade, facade selects protocol and action to process the request
2c Protocol facade generates ServiceContext to call protocol.
Protocol world view is limited to ServiceContext
2d Protocol Action (using bank-protocol-api) is called with ServiceContext (i.e. DenyAuthorization)
2e Protocol returns the result (i.e. Redirection to next consent authorization page or Redirection to ASPSP)

2f Protocol result is handled and translated (i.e. ConsentAcquiredResult trnaslates to Redirection to FinTech)
2i Banking API translates Facade result to 202 or 3xx ResponseEntity with status code and returns to PSU2j PSU returns back to FinTech
